==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ironical
<hw>I*ron"ic*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>ironicus</ets>, Gr. <?/ dissembling: cf. F. <ets>ironique</ets>.
See <er>Irony</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Pertaining to irony; containing, expressing, or
characterized by, irony; <as>as, an <ex>ironical</ex>
remark</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Addicted to the use of irony; given to
irony.</def></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>I*ron"ic*al*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>I*ron"ic*al*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ironing</ent>⟦br⟧
